    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "You keep talking about \"different kinds of stillness,\" but you're treating my grief like a problem to be solved, a sickness to be cured. It isn't. It's a completion. A story reaching its natural, tragic conclusion. Instead of trying to pull me back into the noise, why can't you see the dignity in it? To choose the moment the curtain falls, rather than waiting for the theater to crumble around you? It feels like the only honest thing left to do.",
